Attention all aspiring models, actors, singers and dancers: On May 28, Ramps to Runway Nelspruit and the International Arts Talent Showcase will host the Mpumalanga auditions for this year. This is a platform upon which talented dancers, singers, actors and models from African countries and different walks of life are given local and international career and casting opportunities. ALSO READ: Community members stand together to help pets in distress The main objective of the International Arts Talent Showcase is to empower, educate and provide a platform for individuals from Africa to be discovered by international talent scouts from the United States of America attending this showcase in Johannesburg. This offers international exposure to industry professionals who might invite successfully evaluated artists and models to the largest talent and model convention, the International Modeling & Talent Association (IMTA), creating job opportunities through 33 and Me Talent Agency. The event details are as follows: Date: May 28
Time: Registration starts at 07:45
Venue: eBundu Lodge between White River and Mbombela
For enquiries about the registration process or other matters, contact Ilse van der Merwe on 082 920 2031.